# THE USER'S FALSE-POSITIVE QUESTION: "write file X, run file Y (not X)".
# A process drops an executable X, then launches an UNRELATED image Y.
# Because binding is by file IDENTITY (FileId), the exec's image (Y) != bound
# dropped file (X) -> BINDING_OK fails -> the dropper pattern does NOT accept.
# Expected: NO dropper detection, NO DENY. (engine.md §5.8 rule 1)
ts=1000 op=write actor=500.1 object=file:F_x dir="C:\Temp" entropy=0.40 pe=1
ts=1200 op=exec  actor=500.1 object=proc:600.2 image=F_y cmd="--run"
